browser->server: HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/spa
server-->browser: HTML-code

browser->server: HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.css
server-->browser: main.css

browser->server: HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/spa.js
server-->browser: spa.js

note over browser:
browser starts executing spa.js-code
that requests JSON data from server 
end note

browser->server: HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json
server-->browser: [{ content: "HTML is easy", date: "2019-05-23" }, ...]

note over browser:
browser executes the event handler 
from spa.js that renders notes to display
end note

note over browser:
User enters new note and hits submit
end note

browser->server: AJAX POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/newnote { content: "SPA Note Content" }
server-->browser: Success response or new note data

note over browser:
spa.js handles the response and updates the 
display without a full page reload
end note

note over server:
New notes are not persisted.
They will be lost after server restart.
end note
